The paper discusses the use of millimeter-wave technology in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). The paper also discusses interference cancellation schemes and transceiver structures, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of millimeter-wave technology also falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) as it enables the transmission of high-bandwidth multimedia content. The paper also discusses the practical and regulatory challenges of establishing a hybrid HetNet, which is related to computer architecture (cs.AR) as it involves the design and implementation of a network infrastructure. Finally, the paper discusses the performance advantage of hybrid HetNets, which is related to computer communications (cs.COMM).
